UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2621
1 A RESOLUTION recognizing the filing of the Major Richard Star Act, a bill
2 exploring an opportunity for veterans with disabilities to receive their full United States
3 Department of Defense retirement pay and United States Department of Veterans Affairs
4 disability compensation without offset.
5 WHEREAS, the Major Richard Star Act (H.R. 2102, S. 1032) is proposed
6 bipartisan legislation in 119th Congress that seeks to amend federal law to expand
7 eligibility for concurrent receipt of disability compensation and retirement pay for
8 veterans; and
9 WHEREAS, current federal law requires a dollar-for-dollar offset of disability
10 compensation and retirement pay for a veteran with a disability who was medically
11 retired with fewer than 20 years of service, denying them the full benefits they earned
12 through their service and sacrifice; and
13 WHEREAS, approximately 50,000 veterans with disabilities, including those who
14 sustained combat-related injuries, are affected by this offset, resulting in significant
15 financial hardship, with an average loss of approximately $1,900 per month in earned
16 benefits based on 2022 estimates from the Congressional Budget Office; and
17 WHEREAS, the Major Richard Star Act aims to allow an eligible veteran with a
18 disability to receive both his or her full United States Department of Defense retirement
19 pay and United States Department of Veterans Affairs disability compensation
20 concurrently; and
21 WHEREAS, the bill has garnered significant bipartisan support in Congress with
22 substantial co-sponsorship in both the House of Representatives and the Senate; and
23 WHEREAS, Kentucky is home to approximately 285,000 veterans, one of the
24 larger veteran populations in the nation, with many veterans with disabilities who have
25 served honorably and who are impacted by the current offset policy; and
26 WHEREAS, more than 50 veterans' organizations, including the Wounded Warrior
27 Project, the American Legion, and AMVETS (American Veterans), have endorsed the
Page 1 of 2
