UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2621
1 Major Richard Star Act, highlighting its importance in the veteran community; and
2 WHEREAS, Congress has a duty to care for veterans with disabilities by ensuring
3 they receive the support and benefits earned through their service; and
4 WHEREAS, veterans with disabilities are advocating Congress for the elimination
5 of this offset, and expressing their concerns with the current policy; and
6 WHEREAS, the Major Richard Star Act aims to honor and support all veterans,
7 including those in Kentucky, by ensuring they receive the full benefits they earned
8 through their service, regardless of their length of service; and
9 WHEREAS, the General Assembly recognizes the importance of continued
10 conversations related to veterans with disabilities who have sacrificed for our nation;
11 NOW, THEREFORE,
12 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
13 Kentucky:
14 Section 1. The Senate hereby recognizes the filing of the Major Richard Star
15 Act (H.R. 2102, S. 1032) in the United States Congress, an effort to ensure veterans with
16 disabilities receive their full United States Department of Defense retirement pay and
17 United States Department of Veterans Affairs disability compensation without offset.
18 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
19 Resolution to the President and Vice President of the United States, the Speaker of the
20 United States House of Representatives, the Majority Leader of the United States Senate,
21 members of the Kentucky congressional delegation, and to the sponsor and co-sponsors
22 of this Resolution for distribution.
